  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Women with elective cesarean delivery at 39-42 wks gestation.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Women who shorter than 5'0&quot; in height, those with primary or pregnancy-induced
             hypertension, macrosomia, multiple gestation will be excluded.

          -  Women with known risks of bleeding or potential hysterectomy such as those with
             placenta previa or accrete will also be excluded.

          -  If the epidural catheter cannot be placed within the specific time frame after the
             spinal injection, the case will be excluded.
      </textblock>
